{"cursor":"2567","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n{{Infobox software |name = evasi0n |developer = [https://twitter.com/evad3rs\nevad3rs] (pod2g, MuscleNerd, planetbeing, pimskeks) |screenshot = |caption =\nevasi0n version 1.5.1 |operating system = Microsoft Windows, OS X and Linux\n|website = }}\n\n'evasi0n' (spelled with a zero) is software package that allows the user to\njailbreak and remove limitations imposed on many Apple branded devices running\nApple's iOS software. It is currently capable of jailbreaking iOS devices\nrunning versions between 6.0 to 6.1.2. {{cite web |url =\nhttp://evasi0n.com/ |title = evasi0n - iOS 6.0-6.1 Jailbreak |date = 12 Feb 2013\n|work = Evasi0n |accessdate= 13 Feb 2013 }} \n\nMore than seven million copies were downloaded and presumably installed in the\nfirst four days after release. {{cite web |url = http://appleinsider.com/articles/13/02/12/evasi0n-jailbreaks-over-7m-ios-\ndevices-update-already-available-for-ios-611 |title = Evasi0n 'jailbreaks' 7M\niOS devices, update already available for iOS 6.1.1 |date = 12 Feb 2013 |work =\nApple Insider |accessdate= 13 Feb 2013 }} \n\nThe \"evasi0n\" untethered jailbreak allows users of the iPhone or other hand held\nApple iOS devices to unlock and jailbreak their phones, allowing the owner to\ninstall software that is not approved by Apple. Once the phone is jailbroken,\nthe owner can switch phone carriers, install tethering software such as MyWi\nthat let the phone be used as a wireless hotspot, and download software from\nCydia, an alternate software store based on Advanced Packaging Tool.\n\nThe evasi0n jailbreak is untethered, which means the phone is able to reboot\nwithout having to connect the phone to a computer in order to reload the\nsoftware. This contrasts with tethered jailbreaks which require that the phone\nbe connected to a computer every time it starts in order for the phone to start\nin unlocked mode.\n\nUnfortunately, Apple's Recent Software Update, 6.1.3 is not compatible with\nevasi0n and actually disables the previous jailbreak if iPad, iPhone and iPod\ntouch users download the new Software Update. If you enjoy your jailbroken Apple\ndevice, it is strongly advised that you don't update. If you like having the\nlatest update on your Apple devices however, download and use the latest version\nof redsn0w.\n","linknr":102,"url":"Evasi0n","recorded":1364163236,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Evasi0n&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Evasi0n&action=edit","//en.wikipedia.org/apple-touch-icon.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.wikihiero%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-head","#p-search","/wiki/File:Evasi0n_jailbreak_tool.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/e/ec/Evasi0n_jailbreak_tool.png/300px-Evasi0n_jailbreak_tool.png","/wiki/Software_developer","https://twitter.com/evad3rs","/wiki/Operating_system","/wiki/Microsoft_Windows","/wiki/OS_X","/wiki/Linux","http://evasi0n.com","/wiki/IOS_jailbreaking","/wiki/IOS","#cite_note-1","#cite_note-2","/wiki/IOS_jailbreaking","/wiki/Cydia","/wiki/Advanced_Packaging_Tool","/w/index.php?title=Evasi0n&action=edit&section=1","#cite_ref-1","http://evasi0n.com/","http://evasi0n.com/","#cite_ref-2","http://appleinsider.com/articles/13/02/12/evasi0n-jailbreaks-over-7m-ios-devices-update-already-available-f